WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.889 --> 00:00:02.930
From the Service Operations Workspace homepage,

1
00:00:03.009 --> 00:00:05.570
unresolved work can be accessed through team widgets.

2
00:00:07.309 --> 00:00:07.550
Here,

3
00:00:07.590 --> 00:00:09.550
an unassigned Incident is selected from the

4
00:00:09.550 --> 00:00:11.489
Hosting Services group queue for review.

5
00:00:13.649 --> 00:00:14.550
Before taking ownership,

6
00:00:14.819 --> 00:00:16.020
review the key context.

7
00:00:16.389 --> 00:00:19.129
Priority and SLA timing

9
00:00:19.149 --> 00:00:21.020
help determine how quickly action is needed.

10
00:00:22.659 --> 00:00:24.500
If you're taking responsibility for the incident,

11
00:00:24.569 --> 00:00:26.920
click Assign to Me to assign it to yourself.

12
00:00:28.610 --> 00:00:31.250
This moves the record into the In Progress state.

13
00:00:31.569 --> 00:00:34.240
This signals ownership and updates visibility for others.

14
00:00:34.490 --> 00:00:35.810
Once ownership is established,

15
00:00:35.889 --> 00:00:37.990
the Response SLA is satisfied

16
00:00:38.330 --> 00:00:40.169
and investigation becomes the focus.

17
00:00:41.060 --> 00:00:44.430
Continue to monitor SLA timing throughout the incident lifecycle.

18
00:00:45.470 --> 00:00:46.250
Before acting,

19
00:00:46.689 --> 00:00:47.909
review the issue carefully,

20
00:00:48.369 --> 00:00:49.330
confirm what is happening,

21
00:00:49.490 --> 00:00:50.369
who is affected,

22
00:00:50.650 --> 00:00:53.369
and whether the current classification still makes sense.

23
00:00:54.930 --> 00:00:58.290
A first Worknote should record what has been checked and what happens next.

24
00:00:58.610 --> 00:01:00.930
Meaningful updates make the record useful to others.

25
00:01:05.138 --> 00:01:05.668
At this point,

26
00:01:05.789 --> 00:01:08.728
the incident is actively owned and ready for investigation.
